# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   For an executable, it's typically ignored.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different models/configs/systems, it may lead to conflicts.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock is generally tracked in version control, but can be ignored.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock is generally tracked in version control, but can be ignored.
# pdm.lock

# PEP 582; used by e.g. pdm when STRIP_PROJECT_PYTHON is set to active
__pypackages__/

